THE Nkomazi Magistrates Court on Monday, 1 August released a Mbuzini Community Policing Forum (CPF) member on R1 000 bail. The man (43) was arrested on Sunday, 31 July for possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition in Masibekela Trust near Mbuzini, Mpumalanga. Brigadier Selvy Mohlala confirmed the arrest, saying cops also managed to take a second man in for questioning with the possibility of arrest in relation to a spate of robberies reported around Nkomazi. “The police followed up on information about a man in possession of a firearm with ammunition, and went to a certain house in Masibekela. A search was conducted, resulting in the discovery of a high-calibre firearm with ammunition. The man was arrested and charged. Cops further discovered that the suspect is a member of the CPF,” he said. The matter was postponed to 6 September for further investigation.